decks.notes: The deck is focused on controlling the game by disrupting the opponent's strategy through a combination of counterspells, hand disruption, and removal spells. Glarb, Calamity's Augur serves as the commander and provides card advantage and control elements. The deck includes a variety of powerful control cards such as Force of Will, Thoughtseize, Toxic Deluge, and Drown in the Loch to deal with threats on the board and in the opponent's hand. Additionally, the deck features a mix of card draw spells like Brainstorm and Preordain to filter through the deck and find key pieces. By maintaining control of the game, the deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver the opponent to secure victory.

The deck revolves around utilizing graveyard synergies and sacrifice effects to generate value and overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive game plan. By utilizing cards like Gravecrawler, Bloodghast, and Dread Wanderer, the deck can constantly recur threats from the graveyard while also sacrificing creatures to power up Carrion Feeder and other payoff cards. The deck also includes disruption in the form of hand disruption spells like Thoughtseize, Inquisition of Kozilek, and Duress to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of powerful black cards like Demonic Tutor and Dark Confidant allows the deck to have consistency and additional card advantage. Overall, the deck aims to apply pressure early and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure victory.

This deck focuses on a fast-paced aggressive strategy using the Partner commanders Rograkh and Silas Renn. The deck includes a mix of efficient creatures and disruptive spells to control the board and keep the pressure on the opponent. It utilizes powerful cards like Yuriko, the Tiger's Shadow and Fallen Shinobi to generate card advantage and deal damage quickly. With a combination of evasion, removal, and counter magic, this deck aims to outpace the opponent and secure a victory before they can stabilize. The mana base is optimized for consistency and allows for easy access to all the colors needed to support the aggressive game plan.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by using counterspells, removal spells, and card draw to disrupt the opponent's strategy. Atraxa, Grand Unifier serves as the commander, providing access to multiple colors and adding value to the deck with its proliferate ability. The deck includes a variety of powerful control cards such as Teferi, Hero of Dominaria, Force of Will, and Cryptic Command to manage the board and protect its own game plan. The mana base is optimized for consistency and includes fetch lands and dual lands to ensure the deck can cast its spells efficiently. Overall, the key concept of this deck is to outmaneuver and outlast the opponent through control and resource management.
